           {:contains_hatespeech => false, :title => "The Internet: Blessing or curse?", :date => DateTime.parse('02 December 2012'), :link => "". :author => "Abiola Ajose", :text = %{IT is a known fact that the Internet plays a major role in our day- to-day activities. It has been the most useful technology of the modern times, which helps us not only in our daily lives, but also our Sersonal and professional evelopment. For academic purposes, the Internet is widely used to research or gather information on any subject under the sun. The Internet is, therefore, the largest Encyclopedia for everyone. Besides, with the aid of the several emerging social media, one is able to network without tears. In addition, the Internet is useful in providing fun, be it games, network conferences or online movies, songs, dramas and so on. As a result, it saves the user boredom. It allows for video conferencing, where both the sender and the receiver see each other as they communicate. More importantly, politicians make use of the Internet during electioneering campaigns. It also makes telecommuting possible, where individuals work in their homes and transmit work from home to office, electronically. Moreover, it promotes friendship among the youths, thereby fostering inter-tribal relationship. People get to meet one another on various social networks like email, Facebook, Twitter, 2go and WhatsApp etc. In addition, it gives room for students to learn on their own and at their own convenience. Lectures can be conducted online and feedback is received immediately. Also, the Internet can be used as a medium of advertisement. As a result, advertisement becomes heterogeneous. So, one can easily information on any service or product as may be desired. This enables smooth business transactions without delay. For example, you can buy a flight ticket online without going to the airport. This saves stress and time. You can also pay bills online without getting to the bank. However, a lot of fraudulent activities have been perpetrated via the Internet. People meet one another on the internet for different reasons. Some make friends while some use it as a means to perpetrate evil. There are many cases of crime that have been perpetrated on the internet. For instance, three months ago, a young lady, Cynthia Osokogu, was killed by some guys she made on Facebook. In addition, youths are exposed to pornographic items on the Internet. Nude pictures, which tend to corrupt the mind, are uploaded on the Internet daily. Online activities, its uses and its demerits when misused "Gone are the days when the Internet safety was simply a matter of computer location. Speaking on the use of the internet, Olawale Akanbi. a Chartered Accountant and CEO, Brace Solution, said,   "  Internet,   as   it  is,   is   an international communication network that has been contributed from all information centres around the world. As good as it is, it provides vital information to scholars and individuals who are into business. You can get any definition of any terminology from the use of the Internet. For example, you go to Wikipedia or dictionary on Google, you can get any information. Most times, when I am in class and I discuss a particular terminology, I tell my students to go on Google to get more information on it. This is the essence of information technology. "You can post mails, while sitting in your office and within seconds or hours, you get a feedback. The use of Internet has been transferred to the mobile phones. Thus, while walking on the road or on a commercial bus, you can use the Internet. "Unlike before, we send our credentials or profiles through printed format or hard copy. But with the use of the Internet, you can scan all your information. A student can view any information from the Internet on any write-up, subject or topic. So, students can view the summary of each chapter of a particular book on the Internet. You can also have a free download, which you can use for a period of time. You can buy any textbook online, which means you now have a software copy on the Internet. For instance, ICAN has all its textbooks on the Internet. "Therefore, students don't need to go to the ICAN centre to collect textbooks. They can download free before examination comes and all the textbooks can be printed from the internet. Internet encourages friendship. With internet, you can chat with a friend online. This means that at a particular time, you can be communicating simultaneously with the help of yahoo messenger, face book chat, SMS, chat or through chat .com. There are several Internet social media that encourage relationships and friendship. You can keep business relationship by travelling through Internet. Even, some smart phones now have the Internet service attached to them. One can communicate oneself to the outside world through the Internet. Nigeria has websites that allow the citizens to view the activities of the government. The government communicates to the citizens through the internet and vice versa. "Bills and Acts can be read on the Internet instead of going to the national library. What does it cost to get on the Internet? It is very cheap to get on the Internet. With less than one dollar, which is about 100 naira per hour, it can be available to you. "On the phones, it is less than 10 naira, which makes it available. It encourages business opportunities, as job profiles can be downloaded on the Internet. You can get a job on the Internet, you can sell your goods on it, do foreign exchange, sell your shares and do a lot of things on the Internet. Students can study any material on the internet, watch films and download games on it.
"It, however, has its disadvantages. Youths can get involve into cultism and immoral acts, like watching of Eornographic films and pictures on the iternet. They can learn Dad habit, like abusive language through social network like Facebook chat. They can learn wrong values and meet bad friends. " Parents may not be able to monitor their children because Internet is now on phones. It is very difficult to look at what your child is doing on the Internet. However, parents have to be conscious of educating their children. They also have cordial relationship with them. Parents should allocate time for their children to be used on the Internet. They look for another means of engaging them. Apart from the use of the Internet or computer, the children should have a play time, a family time where you tell them stones that could take their hearts out of the Internet. They should not be attached to it. You as a parent must find a strategy to take your children out of the Internet. A child between 12 and 18 years should have a daily plan. To a mature person, he may not be influenced but can lose some information to the public. Internet does not comply with the rules of confidentiality. Information can be disclosed to anybody. Once your information is on the Internet, you have no privacy. The best way is to passwordy our website or mails. In his view, Mr. Gbadero Diya, a teacher, said, "Internet has been of high importance to every nation. People have been up and doing with the Internet. Different assignments have been done on the Internet making things easy for people. For students, most answers are found on the Internet to most difficult questions. You conduct research and make findings on the Internet. It is very good when we talk of information technology aspect of it. It makes information easy to get nowadays. Unlike in the past, if you want to meet someone who lives in America, you had to travel to America. But now, you can speak with someone who lives in America right insideyour bedroom. This is possible through the Internet with the use of the web cam. Internet has helped ICT to go nationwide. Today, a basic six pupil can operate the computer because he is familiar with the Internet. Yahoo mail, hot mail, Facebook has contributed to the goodies of the Internet. It also encourages distance learning. For somebody who is far away from a particular tutor, he or she can be taught through web cam with the aid of the Internet. Some universities award certificates  to  students  who  study online. You don't have to go to school if you want to study online. You can study online and get a certificate. Internet has been ofgreat importance in several aspects. There is a wise saying that says "there is nothing that has an advantage without a disadvantage". The major disadvantage is the use of the Internet in the wrong sense of it. People exploits make discoveries, do a lot of findings on the Internet. This has led to a lot of negativity. People dupe one another on the "Internet. They call themselves the names they don't bear; they parade themselves as what they are not. Eventually, they lure others to pay money into their accounts .They are popularly called yahoo yahoo. "A lot of things are on me Internet. There are some negative questions, which require negative answers. And whenever you ask such questions, the answer you get is negative and in that process, it brings negative effects of the Internet like people going to pornographic sites. This corrupts peoples' minds and changes their orientation. This creates some imbalance. Although the Internet has a lot of advantages, it also has disadvantages. The Internet has been a two-way thing: the good and the bad. It depends on whichever one you want." More so, Shogbamu Salawa, a Senior Secondary School ( SSS 2) student of Hebron College, Mowe, Ogun State, stated that "The Internet is used to find information based on the topic or your area of study. It helps to get information for more understanding. You can make use of the Wikipedia and Google, if you need to research on any topic. Internet serves as a tool for job opportunities. It can also be used to chat with one's friends. For example, you can meet your old- time friend on the Facebook. Moreover, it corrupts the students through watching pornographic films and nude pictures." In a chat with the Nigerian Compass,Adeleke Babalola, a computer engineer, said the Internet is useful both to the old and young. According to him, "The Internet is useful in the modern society because both old and young benefit from it. The Internet is used to make research via Google, Wikipedia and so on. It is also a fast means of communication. Within few seconds, you can get to someone who is far away with the use of the Internet, either by email, Facebook or Twitter. Through the Internet, you get connected to the outside world through social networking. It helps students to read ahead of the class or examination. It is used by students to do assignment. Also, the syllabus of each subject can be downloaded on the Internet. The benefit of the Internet outweighs its disadvantages. The major disadvantage is the arching of people's password.}}]

